/*
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Source
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
https://learntodroid.com/how-to-switch-between-activities-in-android/

https://github.com/learntodroid/SwitchingBetweenActivities



# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Goal
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
- Create multiple Activities for different screens within your app,
  and migrate data from one page to the other.



# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Steps
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
1. Create Activities layout and class
2. Add link string names to "res > values > strings.xml"
3. Add Both Activities to   "AndroidManifest.xml"
4. Set onClick SwitchActivities



# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Application Flow
# ----------------------------------------------------------------



# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Error Fix
# ----------------------------------------------------------------

WARNING: Hardcoded text
res > values > strings.xml
-  As a general rule, you should never use hardcoded strings in your
layout but always use string resources (which means the all strings
are stored in one separate file where they are easily changeable for
different languages and so on).
- Fix > Resource Value = label/text

ERROR: Can't determine type for tag '<macro name="m3_comp_bottom_app_bar_container_color">?attr/colorSurface</macro>'
- You are working in a older version of Android Studio
Replace :
implementation 'androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.5.1'
implementation 'com.google.android.material:material:1.7.0'
with:
implementation 'androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.4.1'
implementation 'com.google.android.material:material:1.6.0'



 */